cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.MA, cs.IR 

The paper explores the diffusion process and communication patterns in group-buying websites, which involves social interactions and online communication. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the study also involves analyzing large-scale datasets, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the study provides practical management implications, which could be related to cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
